# Pull Request Template — Carbon Mirror Project

Thank you for contributing to the Carbon Mirror Project!  
Please complete the sections below to help maintain clarity, alignment, and quality.

---

## 1. What Does This PR Change?

**Describe the change:**
- What section(s) of the Standard or documentation does this modify?
- Is this a clarification, correction, structural change, or new content?

> _Example: “Clarifies the definition of ‘time-flexible workloads’ in the Timing Mirror.”_

---

## 2. Related Issue

Please link the issue that this PR addresses:

Fixes #____  
Related to #____

> All PRs must correspond to an open issue unless explicitly approved by maintainers.

---

## 3. Type of Change

Select all that apply:

- [ ] Clarification  
- [ ] Correction  
- [ ] Structural reorganization  
- [ ] New explanatory content  
- [ ] Example or table update  
- [ ] Mirror pattern proposal  
- [ ] Tooling reference update  
- [ ] Governance or meta documentation  
- [ ] Other: ____________

---

## 4. Alignment Check

Please confirm the following:

- [ ] This change preserves the neutrality of the Standard (no vendor bias)  
- [ ] This change does not introduce breaking changes without an RFC  
- [ ] This change maintains consistency with Mirror definitions  
- [ ] This change improves clarity or correctness  
- [ ] This change follows Markdown structure conventions  
- [ ] This change aligns with the Carbon Mirror philosophy (precision, clarity, leverage)  

---

## 5. Motivation

**Why is this change needed?**  
Explain the reasoning, the problem being solved, or the improvement being made.

> _Short and focused answers are ideal._

---

## 6. Impact Assessment

**Does this PR impact any of the following?**

- Mirror definitions:  
  - [ ] Yes  
  - [ ] No  

- Certification criteria:  
  - [ ] Yes  
  - [ ] No  

- RFC requirements:  
  - [ ] Yes (attach or reference an RFC)  
  - [ ] No  

- Backward compatibility:  
  - [ ] Maintained  
  - [ ] Potentially affected (explain)  

---

## 7. Additional Notes

Add any contextual information or questions for reviewers here.

---

## 8. Checklist Before Submission

- [ ] My changes match project style and terminology  
- [ ] I have proofread the text for clarity and grammar  
- [ ] I have not introduced marketing or promotional content  
- [ ] I have not mixed unrelated changes  
- [ ] I have reviewed GOVERNANCE.md and CONTRIBUTING.md  
- [ ] I am ready for maintainer review  

---

Thank you for helping strengthen the Carbon Mirror Standard.
Your contribution supports a cleaner, leaner, more intentional digital future.

